onentially small in L^{d-1}. In particular, for all eps>0 the probability\nthat a uniformly chosen independent set from T_{L,d} satisfies ||I \\cap E|-|I\n\\cap O|| \\leq (.25 - eps)L^d is exponentially small in L^{d-1}.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 27 Jul 2010 20:51:19 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-07-29"}
